(7, NULL, NULL, 'University today', 'university-today', '<p><strong>MIREA - Russian Technological University</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>(MIREA, MGUPI, MITHT, VNIITE, RosNIIIT and AP, IPK of the Ministry of Education and Science of the Russian Federation)</strong></p>\n\n<p>Recognized both in&nbsp;Russia and abroad as&nbsp;a&nbsp;modern educational and research center, MIREA&nbsp;&mdash; Russian Technological University combines classical university traditions with modern educational technologies in&nbsp;its work. Since its creation, the higher education institution has always kept up&nbsp;to&nbsp;date constantly expanding the range of&nbsp;academic programs according to&nbsp;the state demand for engineering staff, increasing quality of&nbsp;specialists&rsquo; training and achieving international recognition. MIREA&nbsp;&mdash; Russian Technological University is&nbsp;one of&nbsp;the leaders in&nbsp;the field of&nbsp;training of&nbsp;highly qualified specialists for quickly developing knowledge-intensive branches of&nbsp;science and technology: telecommunications, information and computer technologies, automatic equipment, cybernetics, radio engineering and electronics, chemistry and biotechnologies.</p>\n\n<p>The University implements a&nbsp;unique system of&nbsp;training &laquo;higher education institution&nbsp;&mdash; base chair&nbsp;&mdash; base enterprise&raquo; which provides high efficiency of&nbsp;educational process and guarantees fast adaptation of&nbsp;graduates to&nbsp;real conditions of&nbsp;modern production environment. Today, MIREA&nbsp;&mdash; Russian Technological University has more than 50&nbsp;base chairs at&nbsp;Research Institutes of&nbsp;the Russian Academy of&nbsp;Sciences, design offices and hi-tech enterprises of&nbsp;the Moscow region. Having blended general scientific theoretical training and students&rsquo; practical activities at&nbsp;the largest industry forming innovative enterprises with advanced technologies, MIREA&nbsp;&mdash; Russian Technological University guarantees effective students&rsquo; training which meets the requirements of&nbsp;future employment.</p>\n\n<p>MIREA&nbsp;&mdash; Russian Technological University has the developed network of&nbsp;research centers, scientific laboratories and students design offices.</p>\n\n<p>The faculty of&nbsp;University includes 21&nbsp;fellow and corresponding members of&nbsp;the Russian Academy of&nbsp;Sciences, as&nbsp;well as&nbsp;more than 280 members of&nbsp;other academies and scientific organizations including international ones. Internationally recognized achievements of&nbsp;scientific schools and researchers of&nbsp;MIREA&nbsp;&mdash; Russian Technological University are the basis of&nbsp;strong partnership with universities, scientific centers, production corporations of&nbsp;Germany, France, South Korea, Singapore, Finland, China, Japan and other countries.</p>\n\n<p>International Training Institute of&nbsp;the University has more than 1200 foreign students from 84 countries. There are traditional exchanges of&nbsp;teaching and scientific personnel with European universities for mutual training. Students programs of&nbsp;academic exchange, including double diploma programs are actively developed as&nbsp;well.</p>\n\n<p>MIREA&nbsp;&mdash; Russian Technological University offers various forms of&nbsp;pre-university training and renders career guidance assistance. The University provides different training courses and the evening physical and mathematical school with more than 20&nbsp;branches in&nbsp;sponsored schools of&nbsp;the Moscow region.</p>\n\n<p>MIREA&nbsp;&mdash; Russian Technological University is&nbsp;proud of&nbsp;its highly qualified faculty, modern technical and material resources, vigorous scientific activity and extensive international links.</p>\n', '1'),
(8, NULL, NULL, 'Strategic Development Program', 'strategic-development-program', '<p>The Strategic Development Program (hereinafter &ndash; Program-2020, SDP-2020) of the Federal state budgetary educational institution of higher education &ldquo;MIREA &ndash; Russian Technological University&rdquo; (hereinafter &ndash; RTU MIREA, University) is a general concept for the development of the University for the period between 2020 and 2024, which is a logical continuation of the Strategic Development Program of the University (hereinafter &ndash; SDP-2016), successfully implemented in 2016-2019.<br />\n<br />\nThe Program-2020 is aimed to maintain and increase the results that have been achieved with the account of modern trends in the development of education. The Program sets forth the key goals and objectives, maps out specific areas in education and provides for activities that ensure further development of RTU MIREA at the current stage of the functioning education system.<br />\n<br />\nThe main criteria of this program are based on the indicators of the SDP-2016, that was to ensure the sustainable functioning of the University to achieve qualitatively new results in its activity, given that RTU MIREA was formed via accession to MIREA of the leading Universities in their respective areas: the Moscow State University of Instrument Engineering and Computer Science, Lomonosov Moscow Institute of Fine Chemical Technologies, and a number of educational, academic, research, design, and production organizations, pursuant to orders No. 646 and No. 549 of the Ministry of Education and Science of the Russian Federation dated 09.06.2014 and 29.05.2015 respectively.<br />\n<br />\nThe solution of large-scale tasks facing the Russian higher education, including those goals and objectives set forth in the&nbsp;<em>Education</em>&nbsp;national project, necessitates on-going and future changes in the system of education and determines new goals and ways to achieve them. The SDP-2020 expands the concept of innovation orientation, ensuring the preservation and development of a high-quality system resistant to external and internal challenges in all areas of RTU MIREA activities.<br />\n<br />\nThe Program-2020 has been developed on the principles of consistent and balanced system of key indicators for the University&rsquo;s activities, grouped by areas, specifically: educational activities, research, work with the personnel, international activities, the University&rsquo;s contribution to the socio-economic development of the region, material and technical base, social and cultural infrastructure, University administration, financial and economic activities, social and educational work.<br />\n<br />\nThe SDP-2020 is aimed to map out the ways and identify the means for achieving a new level in all areas of activity that are to ensure the RTU MIREA position as a leading technological university in Russia that contributes to the solution of various issues of social and economic development of the state and society.<br />\n<br />\nThe Strategic Development Program of RTU MIREA for 2020-2024 was approved by the decision of the Academic Board of the University of December 25, 2019, Protocol No. 5.</p>\n', '1'),
(10, NULL, NULL, 'Rector’s Greeting', 'rector’s-greeting', '<p><strong>Greeting of Stanislav A. Kudzh,<br />\nRector of MIREA - Russian Technological University</strong></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Ректор МИРЭА Станислав Алексеевич Кудж\" src=\"https://english.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/358/foto_rektor.jpg\" style=\"float:right; height:280px; width:280px\" /></p>\n\n<p>Dear friends!</p>\n\n<p>I am glad to welcome you on the site of MIREA - Russian Technological University &mdash; one of the leading technical universities! For competitiveness increase and resources concentration in the perspective directions of scientific and academic activities, the Ministry of Education and Science of the Russian Federation made the decision to set up the new federal institution &quot;MIREA - Russian Technological University&quot; which includes:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Moscow State Technical University of Radio Engineering, Electronics and Automation (MGTU MIREA);</li>\n	<li>Moscow State University of Instrument Engineering and Computer Science (MGUPI);</li>\n	<li>Lomonosov Moscow State University of Fine Chemical Technologies (M.V. Lomonosov MITHT);</li>\n	<li>Russian Research Institute of Information Technologies and Automated Design Systems (FGBU RosNII IT and AP);</li>\n	<li>Russian Research Institute of Industrial Art (VNIITE);</li>\n	<li>Institute of Professional Administration and Complex Energy Efficiency (IPK of the Ministry of Education and Science of the Russian Federation);</li>\n	<li>Institute of Modern Educational Technologies and Projects (ISOTP).&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The University faculty conducts scientific research in a number of priority directions, implements multi-level system of training with a wide range of academic programs, constantly improving training process, and introduces information and telecommunication technologies at all levels of scientific and educational process. The innovative nature of the University activities is the key not only to the training of highly qualified specialists, but also to the development of new devices and systems for high-tech industries.</p>\n\n<p>The distinctive feature of the University training is its close cooperation with hi-tech enterprises where base chairs are set up. Our principle is: the University students must participate in scientific and practical work at early stages of training. In the second year students can already apply the gained theoretical knowledge on the premises of the leading enterprises of Moscow and the Moscow region.</p>\n\n<p>At the University there are modern specialized scientific laboratories and educational centers, students&rsquo; design offices and academies of the leading world companies (Cisco, Microsoft, EMC, VMware, Huawei, 1C-Bitriks, etc.)</p>\n\n<p>The most important component of the University&nbsp; development strategy is international scientific and academic cooperation: The University is the member of a number of international associations including&nbsp; the Association of Top Industrial Managers for Europe (T.I.M.E.), the Association of Sino-Russian Technical Universities (ASRTU), the European Association of Research Managers and Administrators (EARMA), the International Association of Universities (IAU), the University League of the Collective Security Treaty Organization (CSTO). A number of the University academic programs are certified according to the international standards.</p>\n\n<p>We pay great attention to the improvement of the University material resources, reconstruction of academic and research buildings, improvement of lecture halls and setting up of world-class research laboratories. The University Students Union works actively arranging a lot of fascinating events for our students.</p>\n\n<p>We keep in memory our glorious past, maintain fine traditions and multiply achievements; we seek to provide our students with universal knowledge and competences which are in high demand, to train them for successful performance in new competitive environment.</p>\n\n<p>It should be noted that the training level of our students is rather high and the University graduates have no employment problems enjoying great demand in all areas of national economy, spheres connected with development and use of nanotechnologies, telecommunication and information systems, robotics, chemical technology, and health care.</p>\n\n<p>I invite you to study and cooperate with MIREA - Russian Technological University!</p>\n\n<p>Yours faithfully,<br />\nS. A. Kudzh, Doctor of Technical Science<br />\nRector of MIREA - Russian Technological University</p>\n', '1'),
