(17, NULL, NULL, 'Education System', 'education-system', '<p><strong>General Information</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>The University offers a wide variety of training services to suit various kinds of persons ranging from pupils uncertain about their aspirations to mature, experienced specialists, scientists, scholars and teachers. Degrees<br />\n	The University conducts training generally resulting in the following degrees: Bachelor&rsquo;s, Engineer&rsquo;s, Master&rsquo;s and PhD. In the framework of education in the Russian Federation there exist the following programs:\n	<ul>\n		<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s/ Engineer&rsquo;s defined as primary education. Persons eligible for these programs must possess a secondary education certificate or a primary or secondary vocational education diploma. Bachelor&rsquo;s program duration is 4 - 4,5 years, while Engineer&rsquo;s is 5 - 5,5 years. Upon completing Bachelor&rsquo;s program, students are certified as a Bachelor and may continue training for a Master&rsquo;s degree.</li>\n		<li>Master&rsquo;s defined as the second level of education. Persons eligible for this program must possess a Bachelor&rsquo;s or Engineer&rsquo;s degree. Master&rsquo;s program duration is 2 years. Upon completing the training, students are certified as a Master and may choose to continue training for a PhD.</li>\n		<li>Postgraduate programs (PhD) defined as the third (final) level of tertiary education. Training is conducted according to postdoc programs lasting 3-4 years (depending on the area of research). Upon completing the training, students are to defend their theses and certified as a Doctor of Philosophy.</li>\n	</ul>\n	<br />\n	<strong>Study modes</strong><br />\n	All modes of study are available at the university, in particular: full time, blended training including distant training.<br />\n	Six-day working week is enforced at MIREA - Russian Technological University. Full-time students study from 9 am to 6 pm, blended learning students study from 6 pm to 9 pm.<br />\n	A number of education programs are partly carried out by means of e-training via the internet. Learning materials, student&rsquo;s guidebooks, tests, etc. are available via e-training provided by the university distant training center.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Base Education System</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>\n	<p>The University training system focuses on broad attraction of leading scientific centers and enterprises of knowledge-intensive branches of science and technology to the educational process.</p>\n\n	<p>At present the University has more than 50 strategic partner enterprises that house base chairs where students major in special disciplines, take traineeship and externship programs, do research for course papers and theses.</p>\n\n	<p>The University training is based on the innovative principle of combination of junior students&rsquo; fundamental training, which exceeds standard levels of a typical engineering higher education institution, with senior students&rsquo; training in future workplaces. Such training is provided by leading scientists and specialists from major scientific institutes of the Russian Academy of Sciences and industrial enterprises which have become the University strategic partners (base enterprises).</p>\n\n	<p>Among strategic partners of the University are:</p>\n	Russian Research Institute of Optic-Physical Metrology (Federal State Unitary Enterprise VNIIOFI)\n\n	<ul>\n		<li>Prokhorov General Physics Institute (GPI RAS)</li>\n		<li>Institute of Informatics Problems of Russian Academy of Sciences (IPI RAN)</li>\n		<li>V.A. Trapeznikov Institute of Control Sciences of Russian Academy of Sciences (ICS RAS)</li>\n		<li>I.S. Bruk Institute of Electronic Control Machinery (OJSC I.S. Bruk INEUM)</li>\n		<li>Infromsvyaz Holding (CJSC Infromsvyaz Holding)</li>\n		<li>Joint Supercomputer Center of the Russian Academy of Sciences (JSC RAS)</li>\n		<li>International Center of Informatics and Electronics (ICIE)</li>\n		<li>Research Institute &rdquo;Voskhod&rdquo; (Federal State Unitary Enterprise RI &ldquo;Voskhod&rdquo;)</li>\n		<li>Research Institute of Distant Radio Communication (OJSC NPK NIIDAR)</li>\n		<li>M. A. Kartsev Research Institute (OJSC NIIVK of M. A. Kartsev)</li>\n		<li>Research Center &ldquo;Kurchatovsky Institute&rdquo; (RC &ldquo;Kurchatov Institute&rdquo;)</li>\n		<li>A.I. Shokin Scientific and Production Enterprise &rdquo;Istok&rdquo; (OJSC NPP Istok)</li>\n		<li>Scientific and Technical Assosiation &ldquo;IRE-Polyus&rdquo; (OJSC NTO IRE-Polyus)</li>\n		<li>Scientific and Technological Center &quot;Kosmonit&quot;</li>\n		<li>OJSC Russian Space Systems (STC &quot;Kosmonit&quot;) of the Award of the Labour Red Banner Research Institute of Automatic Equipment of V. S. Semenikhin (OJSC NIIAA)</li>\n		<li>Dmitry Rogachyov Federal Scientific Clinical Center of Children&#39;s Hematology, Oncology and Immunology of Ministry of Health of the Russian Federation (Federal State Budget Institution FNKTs DGOI of Dmitriy Rogachyov of the Russian Ministry of Health) and others.</li>\n	</ul>\n\n	<p>The base chairs are usually managed by the heads of the enterprises and organizations which house the chairs. Training is provided by the leading scientists and the division heads of these enterprises.</p>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n', '2'),
(18, NULL, NULL, 'Institutes', 'institutes', '<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3><strong><a href=\"institutes.php?institutes_link=institute-of-information-technologies&amp;institutes_detail_link=about-the-institute\">Institute of Information Technologies </a></strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3><strong><a href=\"institutes.php?institutes_link=institute-of-cybernetics&amp;institutes_detail_link=about-the-institute\">Institute of Cybernetics </a></strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3><strong><a href=\"institutes.php?institutes_link=institute-of-radio-engineering-and-telecommunication-systems&amp;institutes_detail_link=about-the-institute\">Institute of Radio Engineering and Telecommunication Systems </a></strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3><strong><a href=\"institutes.php?institutes_link=institute-of-physics-and-technology&amp;institutes_detail_link=about-the-institute\">Institute of Physics and Technology </a></strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3><strong><a href=\"institutes.php?institutes_link=institute-of-integrated-safety-and-special-instrument-engineering&amp;institutes_detail_link=about-the-institute\">Institute of Integrated Safety and Special Instrument Engineering </a></strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3><strong><a href=\"institutes.php?institutes_link=lomonosov-institute-of-fine-chemical-technologies&amp;institutes_detail_link=about-the-institute\">Lomonosov Institute of Fine Chemical Technologies </a></strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '2'),
(19, NULL, NULL, 'Mega-Laboratories', 'mega-laboratories', '<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3><strong><a href=\"mega_lab.php?mega_lab_link=motion-capture-laboratory\">Motion Capture Laboratory </a></strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3><strong><a href=\"mega_lab.php?mega_lab_link=industry-4-0-digital-robotized-production-center\">Industry 4.0: Digital Robotized Production center </a></strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3><strong><a href=\"mega_lab.php?mega_lab_link=laboratory-of-intelligent-autonomous-and-multi-agent-robotic-systems\">Laboratory of Intelligent Autonomous and Multi-Agent Robotic Systems </a></strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3><strong><a href=\"mega_lab.php?mega_lab_link=laboratory-of-analytic-modeling-design-and-digital-prototyping-technologies\">Laboratory of Analytic, Modeling, Design and Digital Prototyping Technologies </a></strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3><strong><a href=\"mega_lab.php?mega_lab_link=center-of-innovative-technologies-in-microelectronics\">Center of Innovative Technologies in Microelectronics </a></strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3><strong><a href=\"mega_lab.php?mega_lab_link=catalytic-and-mass-exchange-processes-center\">Catalytic and Mass Exchange Processes center </a></strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3><strong><a href=\"mega_lab.php?mega_lab_link=immersive-technologies-laboratory\">Immersive Technologies Laboratory </a></strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3><strong><a href=\"mega_lab.php?mega_lab_link=laboratory-for-the-development-and-transfer-of-microfluidic-technologies-dtmt\">Laboratory for the Development and Transfer of Microfluidic Technologies (DTMT) </a></strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3><strong><a href=\"mega_lab.php?mega_lab_link=mobile-robotics-university-laboratory\">Mobile Robotics University Laboratory </a></strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3><strong><a href=\"mega_lab.php?mega_lab_link=research-and-educational-center-for-biosynthesis-isolation-and-purification-of-monoclonal-antibodies-generium\">Research and Educational Center for Biosynthesis, Isolation and Purification of Monoclonal Antibodies (Generium) </a></strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3><strong><a href=\"mega_lab.php?mega_lab_link=radio-electronic-technologies-megalaboratory\">Radio electronic Technologies Megalaboratory </a></strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '2'),
(20, NULL, NULL, 'Additional Education Programs', 'additional-education-programs', '<div><strong>General information</strong>\n<p>Additional education is aimed at the all-round satisfaction of a person&rsquo;s educational needs and is not related to receiving a degree of a higher ranking. That is a form of continuing education when a person, in parallel with receiving a University diploma, obtains another specialty, takes an advanced course in his/her specialty, does a retraining course, or studies languages.</p>\n\n<p>The University implements over 100 different additional education programs:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>professional development programs;</li>\n	<li>professional retraining programs;</li>\n	<li>vocational training programs;</li>\n	<li>additional general education programs;</li>\n	<li>language training programs.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Additional education programs are implemented both in specialized structural additional education units dealing exclusively with additional education programs, and in regular educational structural units which are engaged in programs of both higher and additional education.<br />\nAt the request of the customer, the University can develop and implement a unique program either of advanced training or of professional retraining.</p>\n\n<p>More information on additional education programs (advanced training and professional retraining programs, general education programs) can be obtained from the Institute of Additional Education, by phone +7 499 215 65 65, ext. 1026 or by e-mail:&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:fpk@mirea.ru\">fpk@mirea.ru&nbsp;</a>.</p>\n\n<p>More information about vocational training programs can be obtained at the MIREA Driver Training Center (driving school, motorcycle school, etc.) by phone +7 499 681 65 65, or by e-mail:&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:UTC@mirea.ru\">UTC@mirea.ru</a>.</p>\n</div>\n', '2'),
(21, NULL, NULL, 'Welcome to RTU MIREA', 'welcome-to-rtu-mirea', '<div>\n<p><strong>Welcome to RTU MIREA</strong></p>\n\n<p>MIREA &ndash; Russian Technological University is a leading state university formed as a result of the merger of the Moscow Institute of Radio Engineering, Electronics and Automation (MIREA), MGUPI, MITHT named after M.V. Lomonosov and a number of research institutions. The University is currently offering most popular educational programs in IT, computer security, electronics, radio engineering, robotics, chemistry and other spheres; it also provides broad opportunities for further education.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Advantages of RTU MIREA:</strong><br />\n&nbsp;State university<br />\n&nbsp;License<br />\n&nbsp;Accreditation</p>\n\n<p><strong>All levels of education:</strong></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;College<br />\n&nbsp;Bachelor&#39;s degree<br />\n&nbsp;Specialist&#39;s degree</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;Master&rsquo;s degree<br />\n&nbsp;Postgraduate study<br />\n&nbsp;Doctoral studies</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://english.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/4dd/2Pu54thbhIM.jpg\" style=\"width:100%\" /></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://english.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/e27/roskosmos.png\" style=\"height:20%\" /></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://english.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/a8f/rostekh.png\" style=\"height:20%\" /></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://english.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/1e7/rosatom.png\" style=\"height:20%\" /></p>\n\n<p>RTU MIREA closely cooperates with the leading enterprises of priority industries where students acquire working skills while still studying at the University. It is this approach to training that guarantees University graduates employment in interesting and well paid-for positions.</p>\n\n<p><br />\n<strong>The Potential of 3 Universities</strong></p>\n\n<p>MIREA - Russian Technological University is the result of the association of MIREA, MGUPI, MITHT named after M.V. Lomonosov and a number of large educational, research and development, design and production organizations. The restructuring has led to a synergy effect and increased manifold the already accumulated knowledge, expertise, human resources, material and technical base of the University.</p>\n\n<p><br />\n<strong>Qualified academic staff</strong></p>\n\n<p>Among the University staff, there are members of the Russian Academy of Sciences and other Academies, professors and doctors of sciences. 77 % of the staff have academic degrees and titles. Leading foreign scholars and professors are invited to lecture, conduct courses in various subjects and disciplines. Starting fr om their 3d year students are trained in specialized departments by practicing designers, chief engineers and even CEOs of enterprises.</p>\n\n<p><br />\n<strong>State University</strong></p>\n\n<p>Upon graduation from MIREA &ndash; Russian Technological University &ndash; graduates receive a state diploma recognized both in Russia and abroad</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;<br />\n<strong>Congenial environment for studying and leisure</strong></p>\n\n<p>The educational and training process is organized across 7 campuses located fairly close to Moscow metro stations. All of them have up-to-date equipment, multi-service infrastructure, and high-speed Wi-Fi. There are cafes, libraries, and conference rooms in the campuses territories.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><br />\n<strong>Over4,000 budget places</strong></p>\n\n<p>Over 4,000 budget places are allocated annually to the first-year applicants. The University provides discounts or allows installment payments for students studying on the commercial basis. With good academic performance and subject to the availability of places in the specific program, it is possible to be transferred to a budget system.</p>\n\n<p><br />\n<strong>Six student dormitories in Moscow</strong></p>\n\n<p>The campus of RTU MIREA accommodates over 3,500 nonresident students, post-graduates and doctoral students. The buildings are comfortable to live in, study, go in for sports and engage in recreational activity. If additional places are needed, the University accommodates its students in dormitories of partner universities.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Education in RTU MIREA is a guarantee for successful employment</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>&gt;99%</strong><br />\nGraduates employed</p>\n\n<p><strong>&gt;50</strong><br />\nMajor partner enterprises</p>\n\n<p><strong>&gt;300</strong><br />\nEmployers</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://english.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/e27/roskosmos.png\" style=\"height:30px; width:30px\" /></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://english.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/a8f/rostekh.png\" style=\"height:30px; width:30px\" /></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://english.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/1e7/rosatom.png\" style=\"height:30px; width:30px\" /></p>\n\n<p><strong>23%</strong><br />\nof students participate in R&amp;D</p>\n\n<h3>Training programs in various areas of study and specialties:</h3>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://english.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/4e9/pie_chart.png\" style=\"width:70%\" /></p>\n\n<p>IT and automation&nbsp;<strong>24.3%</strong></p>\n\n<p>IT Engineering and Technologies&nbsp;<strong>15.6%</strong></p>\n\n<p>Economics and Management&nbsp;<strong>14.9%</strong></p>\n\n<p>Chemistry&nbsp;<strong>14.1%</strong></p>\n\n<p>Security&nbsp;<strong>12.9%</strong></p>\n\n<p>Electronics and nanotechnology&nbsp;<strong>7.6%</strong></p>\n\n<p>Radio engineering and telecommunications&nbsp;<strong>6.9%</strong></p>\n\n<p>Jurisprudence&nbsp;<strong>2.6%</strong></p>\n\n<p>Design&nbsp;<strong>0.8%</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>&nbsp;Demand for graduates</strong></p>\n\n<p>99 % of University graduates are employed, including those working in senior positions. They are highly in demand in partner companies and at industrial enterprises in general.</p>\n\n<p><strong>&nbsp;Order of the day educational programs</strong></p>\n\n<p>The University has over 500 educational programs. The University is implementing each of them because of its obligation to the students to provide only relevant knowledge and useful skills that will further be helpful in students finding decent and well-paid work.</p>\n\n<p><strong>&nbsp;&gt;50 partner companies</strong></p>\n\n<p>RTU MIREA closely cooperates with high-tech enterprises: Rostech, Rosatom, Roscosmos corporations and others. Students study some of the disciplines on site getting to know the real production process and, having proven successful, get a job at the enterprise. Students usually start working in their 3rd year, and by the time they graduate from the University, enter the labor market having acquired practical experience. Enterprises employ such specialists much more willingly.</p>\n\n<p><strong>&nbsp;Training to work in high-tech areas</strong></p>\n\n<p>Students of RTU MIREA are engaged in the implementation of R &amp; D and design and construction work in electronics, radio engineering, aerospace industry and other high-tech industries using advanced and expensive equipment in the University research centers and laboratories. They are also actively participating in international research projects.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Opportunities for additional education</strong></p>\n\n<p>For our students, we strive to create feasible opportunities for professional growth and personal development and, thus, ensure a successful start in the labor market for them. University students have ample opportunities to get additional education: there is a choice of joint programs with major IT companies (Cisco, Microsoft, Huawei, 1C-Bitrix, etc.), foreign language courses (English, German, Spanish, Japanese, etc.), MBA, joint programs with the All-Russian State Television and Radio Broadcasting Company - Academy of TV, auto and motorcycle school and more. Training takes place at the University sites, and prices tend to be much lower than in commercial structures.</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://english.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/a95/girl.jpg\" /></p>\n\n<p><strong>&nbsp;Study abroad</strong></p>\n\n<p>Over 60 foreign partner universities<br />\nAbout 40 countries wh ere students can take internships and exchange programs<br />\nMost student programs are free.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Joint programs with IT companies:</strong></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://english.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/d82/content_img.png\" /></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://english.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/55c/content_img.png\" /></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://english.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/d97/content_img.png\" /></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://english.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/d7b/content_img.png\" /></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://english.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/815/content_img.png\" /></p>\n\n<p><strong>Learning foreign languages</strong></p>\n\n<table align=\"left\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>English</td>\n			<td>Italian</td>\n			<td>Chinese</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>German</td>\n			<td>Spanish</td>\n			<td>Japanese</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>French</td>\n			<td>Swedish</td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Preparation to exams</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>LCCI International Qualifications</li>\n	<li>FCE, CAE, TOEFL, IELTS</li>\n	<li>Nihongo Noryoku Shiken</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>&nbsp;MBA</strong><br />\n<br />\n<strong>&nbsp;TV Academy</strong><br />\n<br />\n<strong>&nbsp;Driving school</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>&nbsp;Motocycle school</strong><br />\n<br />\n<strong>&nbsp;Marine school</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Exciting student life</strong></p>\n<img src=\"https://english.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/7e4/content_img-_1_.png\" style=\"width:100%\" />\n<p><img src=\"https://english.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/b54/sumirea_2.jpg\" /></p>\n\n<p><strong>&nbsp;Exciting student life</strong></p>\n\n<p>The University created the Student Union which unites all activists of the University. Free classes are organized for students in theater, vocal and dance studios, there is a school of guitar playing. KVN (wits and humor competition), the OPEN AIR festival, the School of Survival; there are photo and mountaineering clubs, pedagogical, rescue, search and archaeological teams.</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://english.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/e2f/sumirea_3.jpg\" /></p>\n\n<p><strong>&nbsp;Sports opportunities</strong></p>\n\n<p>The University has three modern large sports complexes, wh ere everyone can attend numerous sports sections: from fitness and cheerleading to football and powerlifting. On the territory of the complexes there are indoor tennis courts, volleyball and basketball courts, a swimming pool and even a climbing wall.</p>\n\n<p><strong>&nbsp;Student union</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Over 7,000 members</li>\n	<li>More than 20 major events annually</li>\n	<li>Social and legal protection of students</li>\n	<li>Organization of leisure and recreation, sporting events</li>\n	<li>Youth initiatives support</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>&nbsp;7 sports sections</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Football</li>\n	<li>Volleyball</li>\n	<li>Basketball</li>\n	<li>Table tennis</li>\n	<li>Badminton</li>\n	<li>Karate</li>\n	<li>Boxing</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>&nbsp;Science and education</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>33 student scientific associations</li>\n	<li>Radio engineering</li>\n	<li>Cyber security</li>\n	<li>Mobile Development</li>\n	<li>Sensor networks</li>\n	<li>Quantum electronics</li>\n	<li>Fine chemical technologies</li>\n	<li>English philology and culture and dozens of other activities</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>&nbsp;University teams</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Football</li>\n	<li>Mini football</li>\n	<li>Basketball</li>\n	<li>Volleyball</li>\n	<li>Tennis</li>\n	<li>Swimming</li>\n	<li>Chess</li>\n	<li>Cybersport</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Every year the teams participate in district, city and All-Russian competitions and Moscow student sports games</p>\n\n<p><strong>&nbsp;Interest groups</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Pedagogical</li>\n	<li>Rescue</li>\n	<li>Search and Archaeological</li>\n	<li>Building</li>\n	<li>Social</li>\n	<li>Career guidance</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>&nbsp;Student Creative Club</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>over 20 creative teams</li>\n	<li>over 300 students</li>\n	<li>Amateur club</li>\n	<li>Dance studio</li>\n	<li>Guitar school</li>\n	<li>Photo studio</li>\n	<li>Chamber choir</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The Club members annually participate in Moscow, Russian and international festivals.</p>\n</div>\n', '3'),
(22, NULL, NULL, 'Admission Procedure', 'admission-procedure', '<div>\n<p><strong>RTU MIREA admission requirements for foreigners</strong><br />\nThe&nbsp;training can be state-funded as well as contract-based depending on&nbsp;the&nbsp;citizenship, &laquo;compatriot&raquo; status and&nbsp;educational background of&nbsp;the&nbsp;Applicant.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Foreign citizens may apply for state-funded openings</strong>&nbsp;within the quota established by the Government of the Russian Federation (by assignment of the Ministry of Science and Higher Education of the Russian Federation).<br />\nOfficial site for selection of foreign citizens by quota:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://future-in-russia.com/\">https://future-in-russia.com/</a>.</p>\n\n<p><strong>For any questions on admission please contact the Study Office of the Institute of International Education:</strong><br />\ntel.: +7&nbsp;495 433-03-22<br />\ne-mail:&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:imo@mirea.ru\">imo@mirea.ru</a></p>\n\n<p><strong>Foreign citizens with insufficient Russian language proficiency may receive training under the Pre-university Training Department for Foreign Citizens programs:</strong><br />\ntel.: +7&nbsp;499 215-65-65&nbsp;ext.&nbsp;1104<br />\ne-mail:&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:avagimyanc@mirea.ru\">avagimyanc@mirea.ru</a></p>\n\n<p><strong>Regarding invitations and migration registration, please contact the International Relations Department:</strong><br />\ntel.: +7&nbsp;499 215-65-65&nbsp;ext.&nbsp;1082, 1123<br />\ne-mail:&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:burceva@mirea.ru\">burceva@mirea.ru</a></p>\n\n<p><strong>Office hours:&nbsp;</strong>Monday &mdash; Thursday (9:00&nbsp;AM &mdash; 6:00&nbsp;PM), Friday (9:00&nbsp;AM &mdash; 5:00&nbsp;PM)</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<table border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>&nbsp;\n			<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Information on legalization and verification of the equivalence of foreign educational certificates is available on the website of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nic.gov.ru/\">National Information Center</a>(Glaveskperttsentr).&nbsp;<br />\n			&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n&nbsp;\n\n<p>Foreign citizens submit the following documents to the Institute of International Education for admission to the first year of the&nbsp;<strong>BACHELOR&#39;S DEGREE PROGRAM:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>the original certificate of secondary (complete) general education (or the original education certificate of a foreign state recognized as the equivalent of the certificate of secondary (complete) general education (high school diploma) in the Russian Federation and the annex thereto specifying the subjects on the academic curriculum;</li>\n	<li>a notarized translation into Russian of the above-mentioned foreign education document and all its annexes;</li>\n	<li>passport (an ID);</li>\n	<li>a notarized translation into Russian of the passport (an ID);</li>\n	<li>a foreign education recognition certificate (except for the cases when recognition of the document is not required);</li>\n	<li>6 identical 3x4 cm photographs on matte paper.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Foreign citizens submit the following documents to the Institute of International Education for admission to the first year of the&nbsp;<strong>MASTER&#39;S DEGREE PROGRAM</strong>:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>the original certificate of higher education (or the original education certificate of a foreign state recognized as the equivalent of the certificate of a bachelor&#39;s, specialist&#39;s, or master&#39;s degree in the Russian Federation and the annex thereto specifying the subjects on the academic curriculum;</li>\n	<li>a notarized translation into Russian of the above-mentioned foreign education document and all its annexes;</li>\n	<li>passport (an ID);</li>\n	<li>a notarized translation into Russian of the passport (an ID);</li>\n	<li>a foreign education recognition certificate (except for the cases when recognition of the document is not required);</li>\n	<li>6 identical 3x4 cm photographs on matte paper.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Each foreign state education certificate (except education certificates of the countries with which the Russian Federation has concluded agreements on mutual recognition of education) the Applicant should have a document confirming the equivalence of the educational certificate to obtain which, please, apply to the Expert Center (<a href=\"https://nic.gov.ru/\">Glaveskperttsentr</a>) of the Federal Service for Supervision in the Sphere of Education and Science at the address: 51 Lyusinovskaya St., 115093 Moscow, Russia.</p>\n\n<p><strong>After admission to the University, foreign citizens are required to provide the following documents</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>to the Institute of International Education:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>medical&nbsp;certificate&nbsp;issued&nbsp;by&nbsp;the&nbsp;official&nbsp;health&nbsp;authority&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;sending&nbsp;country,&nbsp;with&nbsp;translation&nbsp;into&nbsp;Russian,&nbsp;or the&nbsp;086-U&nbsp;form;</li>\n	<li>HIV negative certificate (document);</li>\n	<li>blood test for syphilis;</li>\n	<li>X-ray examination certificate.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>to International Relations Department:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>passport (an ID);</li>\n	<li>a&nbsp;migration&nbsp;card&nbsp;with&nbsp;a&nbsp;stamp&nbsp;on&nbsp;crossing&nbsp;the&nbsp;border of&nbsp;the&nbsp;Russian&nbsp;Federation&nbsp;specifying&nbsp;the&nbsp;purpose&nbsp;of&nbsp; arrival&nbsp;- &ldquo;study&rdquo;&nbsp;for&nbsp;full-time&nbsp;students;</li>\n	<li>visa (for study) for citizens from countries with a visa regime;</li>\n	<li>a voluntary medical insurance policy (if it is not available, it is possible to obtain one in the International Relations Office);</li>\n	<li>2&nbsp;identical 3x4&nbsp;cm color photographs&nbsp;on&nbsp;matte&nbsp;paper;</li>\n	<li>residence&nbsp;permit,&nbsp;temporary&nbsp;residence&nbsp;permit&nbsp;(if&nbsp;available);</li>\n	<li>TIN (if available);</li>\n	<li>personal insurance policy number (if available);</li>\n	<li>copy of employment record (if available);</li>\n	<li>marriage&nbsp;certificate,&nbsp;child&#39;s&nbsp;birth&nbsp;certificate (if&nbsp;any);</li>\n	<li>personal profile (to be completed in A-304).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n', '3'),
(23, NULL, NULL, 'Pre-university Training Department', 'pre-university-training-department', '<div>\n<p><strong>Pre-university Training Department for foreign citizens</strong></p>\n\n<p>If you are planning to receive a high-quality higher education in Russia, but do not speak Russian or do not speak Russian sufficient enough, we suggest that you take a course at the Pre-university Training Department. It helps foreign citizens to later join Russian-taught full-degree programmes. Over 10 months of intensive study, students improve their basic language skills (reading, listening, speaking, and writing), study in a chosen academic field (engineering), and adapt to the new educational environment. Upon completing preparatory year, students are expected to possess intermediate-level language skills (CEFR level B1, TRKI level 1) and be ready to enter the Russian-taught full-degree programs at RTU MIREA and other Russian universities.</p>\n\n<p>For further information, please, contact Victoria A. Avagimyanc, Head of Pre-university Training Department for foreign citizens, by phone +7 499 215-65-65 ext. 1104 or e-mail:&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:avagimyanc@mirea.ru\">avagimyanc@mirea.ru</a>.</p>\n</div>\n', '3'),
(24, NULL, NULL, 'Migration Regulations', 'migration-regulations', '<div>\n<h2>Regarding invitations and migration registration, please contact the International Relations Department:</h2>\n\n<p>tel.: +7&nbsp;499 215-65-65&nbsp;ext.&nbsp;1082, 1123<br />\ne-mail:&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:burceva@mirea.ru\">burceva@mirea.ru</a></p>\n\n<p><strong>Office hours:</strong>&nbsp;Monday &mdash; Thursday (9:00&nbsp;AM &mdash; 6:00&nbsp;PM), Friday (9:00&nbsp;AM &mdash; 5:00&nbsp;PM)</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Procedure of migration registration and residence regulations for foreign citizens arriving for training at RTU MIREA</strong></p>\n<a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/2e1/Pravila-migratsionnogo-ucheta.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Правила миграционного учета</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/f44/Migration-registration-rules.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Migration registration rules</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/2a9/Normas-del-registro-migratorio.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Normas del registro migratorio</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/431/R_gles-de-migration.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">R&egrave;gles de migration</a>\n\n<p><strong>1. Basic rules of stay in the territory of the Russian Federation for a foreign citizen studying at RTU MIREA</strong></p>\n\n<p>1.1. A foreign citizen arriving to the Russian Federation to study at RTU MIREA is obliged to observe the laws of the Russian Federation: the Federal Law of 15/8/1996 No. 114-FZ &quot;Concerning departure from the Russian Federation and entrance to the Russian Federation procedures&quot;, the Federal Law of 25/7/2002 No. 115-FZ &quot;Concerning the legal status of foreign citizens in the Russian Federation&quot;, the Federal Law of 18/7/2006 No. 109-FZ &quot;Concerning migration registration of foreign citizens and stateless persons in the Russian Federation&quot;, the Order of the Government of the Russian Federation of 15/1/2007 No. 9 &quot;Concerning procedure of migration registration of foreign citizens and stateless persons in the Russian Federation&quot;.</p>\n\n<p>1.2. According to the migration laws of the Russian Federation, foreign citizens and stateless persons who have arrived in the territory of the Russian Federation shall be required to register at the place of stay in the Ministry of Internal Affairs of Russia on migration issues within 7 working days from the date of entry.</p>\n\n<p>1.2.1. Exceptions shall cover citizens of the Republic of Kazakhstan, the Republic of Armenia, the Kyrgyz Republic, the Republic of Belarus required to be registered within 30 days, and the Republic of Tajikistan &ndash; within 15 days from the date of entry.</p>\n\n<p>1.3. When returning to the territory of the Russian Federation after going abroad, or after staying in another city of the Russian Federation for more than 7 days, a foreign citizen shall file the necessary documents to the International Relations Department of RTU MIREA (room A-304) within 1 working day (if it is a day off, the first working day after it) for the renewal of primary migration registration.</p>\n\n<p>1.4. During his/her stay in the territory of the Russian Federation, a foreign citizen shall have with him a coupon tear-off part of the arrival notice (registration) with the mark of the territorial migration authority of the Ministry of Internal Affairs on migration registration, the national passport, visa (for countries with a visa regime) and the migration card (with a mark of the Ministry of Internal Affairs on migration registration for countries with a visa-free regime).</p>\n\n<p>1.4.1. In case of loss (damage) by a foreign citizen of a notice of arrival (registration), the national passport, a migration card, he/she shall apply to the International Relations Department within 1 day from the moment of the loss of documents.</p>\n\n<p>1.5. At least 6 months before the expiration of the national passport, a foreign citizen shall prolong or replace it with a new one and submit it to the International Relations Department to make changes in the personnel file.</p>\n\n<p>1.6. Upon receipt of a temporary residence permit, residence permit or passport of the Russian Federation, a foreign citizen within 3 days shall provide copies of documents to the International Relations Department to make changes in the personnel file.</p>\n\n<p>1.7. When entering the territory of the Russian Federation, foreign citizens shall be required to purchase a voluntary medical insurance policy by contacting the International Relations Department or insurance companies operating in the territory of Moscow and Moscow Region.</p>\n\n<p>1.8. A foreign citizen who has terminated or completed his/ her studies at the RTU MIREA shall leave the territory of the Russian Federation within 3 days from the date of dismissal.</p>\n\n<p>1.9. When a foreign citizen transfers to study at RTU MIREA from another educational institution or is enrolled after graduating from the preparatory department of another institution to RTU MIREA, the departure from the Russian Federation shall not be required. Documents shall be made out according to the general rules.</p>\n\n<p><strong>2. Migration registration of foreign citizens</strong></p>\n\n<p>2.1. According to the Federal Law of 27/6/2018 № 163-FZ &quot;On Amending the Federal Law &quot;On migration registration of foreign citizens and stateless persons in the Russian Federation&quot; migration registration is carried out at the actual residential address of foreign citizens.</p>\n\n<p>2.2. Migration registration of foreign citizens studying on a contractual basis shall cover the period of tuition payment; of foreign citizens who have entered the budget form of education - one academic year.</p>\n\n<p>2.3. Foreign citizens who arrived to study at RTU MIREA and received accommodation in the dormitory of RTU MIREA are required to file to the International Relations Department, within 1 working day, the following documents to receive a notification of arrival and migration registration (registration):</p>\n\n<p>- passport;</p>\n\n<p>- visa (for countries with a visa regime);</p>\n\n<p>- the original of migration card with the Russian Federation border crossing mark and indication of the purpose of arrival &quot;study&quot;.</p>\n\n<p>2.4. For the extension of registration it is necessary to provide the documents specified in sub-paragraph 2.3. to the International Relations Department in 30 days prior to the registration expiration.</p>\n\n<p>2.5. Foreign citizens who do not reside in the dormitories of RTU MIREA shall independently register their migration records at the actual residence address and submit to the International Relations Department the documents listed below:</p>\n\n<p>- copy of the passport;</p>\n\n<p>- copy of the migration card;</p>\n\n<p>- copy of the migration registration notice.</p>\n\n<p><strong>3. Registration and prolongation of a multiple entry visa</strong></p>\n\n<p>3.1. When entering the territory of the Russian Federation with a primary (single) visa, the International Relations Department issues a multiple entry visa for the term of tuition (for foreign citizens studying on a contractual basis), but not exceeding one academic year (budget form).</p>\n\n<p>3.2. Foreign citizens from the countries with visa regime arriving for the admission to RTU MIREA are obliged to provide the following documents to the International Relations Department for migration registration and multiple-entry visa within one working day (if it is a day off, the first working day after it):</p>\n\n<p>- passport;</p>\n\n<p>- visa;</p>\n\n<p>- the original of migration card with the Russian Federation border crossing mark and indication of the purpose of arrival &quot;study&quot;.</p>\n\n<p>- two photos 3х4 cm in&nbsp;size;</p>\n\n<p>- paid receipt of the state tax (1,600 RUB).</p>\n\n<p>3.3. To extend a multi-entry visa term it is necessary to provide the documents specified in sub-paragraph 3.2. to the International Relations Department 45 days prior to the visa expiration.</p>\n</div>\n', '3'),
(25, NULL, NULL, 'International Cooperation', 'international-cooperation', '<div>\n<p>International scientific and educational cooperation is the most important component of the general development strategy of the University. This activity is carried out within programs of cooperation with leading foreign higher education institutions by the implementation of joint research work, holding of conferences and practical seminars, exchange of teaching staff and development of students&rsquo; mobility.<br />\n<br />\n<strong>At present the University has close links with more than 46 universities, institutes, schools and companies from 18 countries.</strong><br />\nThe University is a member of the international associations:<br />\n&bull;<a href=\"https://www.time-association.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Top Industrial Managers for Europe Association (T.I.M.E.);</a><br />\n&bull;<a href=\"https://wdo.org/\" target=\"_blank\">World design Organization (WDO);</a><br />\n&bull;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://asrtu.cup-russia.ru/\" target=\"_blank\">Association of Sino-Russian Technical Universities (ASRTU);</a><br />\n&bull;<a href=\"http://www.iau-aiu.net/\" target=\"_blank\">International Association of Universities (IAU);</a><br />\n&bull;<a href=\"http://www.earma.org/\" target=\"_blank\">European Association of Research Managers and Administrators (EARMA);</a><br />\n&bull;<a href=\"http://www.osadl.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Open Source Automation Development Lab eG (OSADL);</a><br />\n&bull;<a href=\"https://www.ethernet-powerlink.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Ethernet POWERLINK Standartization Group (EPSG);</a><br />\n&bull;<a href=\"https://odkb-csto.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Collective Security Treaty Organization (CSTO).</a><br />\n<br />\nWithin the international scientific cooperation there are created joint educational and scientific departments, joint scientific research is carried out at the University.<br />\n<br />\n<strong>One of the key directions of the international cooperation is the development of academic mobility:</strong><br />\n&bull; development and implementation of joint educational programs directed at providing students with the possibility of training at foreign higher education institutions, and also obtaining two diplomas &mdash; of RTU MIREA and of a foreign partner university<br />\n&bull; leading professors and teachers&rsquo; exchange with foreign partner higher education institutions for the purpose of lecturing, holding master classes, and participating in joint scientific research.</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><a href=\"https://english.mirea.ru/international/international-cooperation/\">International Cooperation</a></li>\n	<li><a href=\"https://english.mirea.ru/international/international-partners/\">International Partners</a></li>\n	<li><a href=\"https://english.mirea.ru/international/international-associations/\">International Associations</a></li>\n	<li><a href=\"https://english.mirea.ru/international/international-science/\">International Science</a></li>\n	<li><a href=\"https://english.mirea.ru/international/exchange-programs/\">Exchange Programs</a></li>\n	<li><a href=\"https://english.mirea.ru/international/rtu-mirea-in-rankings/\">RTU MIREA in Rankings</a></li>\n	<li><a href=\"https://english.mirea.ru/international/international-relations-department/\">International Relations Department</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n', '4');
