https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/1d6/DSC06775.JPG\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/035/DSC06756.JPG\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/035/DSC06756.JPG\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/857/DSC06781.JPG\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/857/DSC06781.JPG\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/1c9/Risunok10.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/1c9/Risunok10.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/8fd/Risunok11.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/8fd/Risunok11.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/820/R8A6800.JPG\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/820/R8A6800.JPG\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/da6/Risunok13.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/da6/Risunok13.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/76f/Risunok9.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/76f/Risunok9.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/b9c/Risunok12.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/b9c/Risunok12.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '5.jfif', '5'),
(6, NULL, NULL, 'Catalytic and Mass Exchange Processes center', 'catalytic-and-mass-exchange-processes-center', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The training and research center entitled &ldquo;Catalytic and Mass Exchange Processes&rdquo; operates on the premises of the Lomonosov Institute of Fine Chemical Technologies. It encompasses the Departments of Physical Chemistry, General Chemical Technology, Chemistry, and Basic Organic Synthesis Technology. These departments have extensive experience in training and research in the field of catalytic processes and systems, and energy-efficient reaction mixture separation processes.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Center has state-of-the-art equipment and instruments designed to explore and develop techniques to obtain various chemical products.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Center&rsquo;s equipment includes:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n- all-purpose flow-circulation units equipped with all features required for testing and studying catalysts within a wide range of temperatures and pressures;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n- modern analytical instruments: gas chromatographs, chromatography-mass spectrometers for various purposes;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n- benches for experimental study of mass exhcange processes (rectification, liquid extraction, absorption).<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Center takes to a new level the quality of academic instruction and practical training of undergraduate and graduate students who can acquire new engineering competencies and research skills.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Center&rsquo;s facilities are also in demand among undergraduates and graduates majoring in chemistry and chemical technology.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/453/R8A5123.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/453/R8A5123.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/1ff/R8A6591.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/1ff/R8A6591.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/94c/R8A6567.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/94c/R8A6567.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/ed4/R8A6601.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/ed4/R8A6601.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/e92/R8A6614.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/e92/R8A6614.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/9e6/R8A6640.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/9e6/R8A6640.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/305/R8A6652.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/305/R8A6652.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/565/R8A6694.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/565/R8A6694.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/c49/R8A6653.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/c49/R8A6653.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/fd2/R8A6671.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/fd2/R8A6671.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/759/R8A6683.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/759/R8A6683.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/644/R8A6702.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/644/R8A6702.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/d70/R8A6713.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/d70/R8A6713.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/e1a/R8A6747.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/e1a/R8A6747.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/210/R8A6752.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/210/R8A6752.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n', '6.jpg', '6'),
(7, NULL, NULL, 'Immersive Technologies Laboratory', 'immersive-technologies-laboratory', '<p>The laboratory was created to unlock the potential of immersion for operators in augmented reality environments (virtual, augmented, and mixed), and to teach individual and/or group actions in simulated environments.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPost-graduates, undergraduates and graduates of the IT Institute have access to the laboratory where they are engaged in developing environments and applications of augmented reality, analyzing different aspects of applying these technologies in production, design, education, research, and various creative activities.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe equipment listed below is available in the laboratory:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&bull; virtual reality devices - Oculus Quest, HTC Vive Pro Eye, HTC Vive Cosmos;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&bull; augmented reality devices - Epson Moverio Pro BT-2200, ODG R-7;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&bull; mixed reality devices - Magic Leap One and Microsoft HoloLens 2;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&bull; laptop computers in the form of Zotac VR Go 2.0 backpacks;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&bull; TACTOT tactile suits with arm and leg armor;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&bull; a stand for simultaneous work of up to four operators.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe available equipment will allow one or several operators to get immersed in any mixed reality environment with the use of their own visual perception and the reconstruction of physical sensations via the body and limbs exposure to the external effects.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/83f/IMG_20200807_224450.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/83f/IMG_20200807_224450.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/55f/IMG_20200807_224517.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/55f/IMG_20200807_224517.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/9b8/IMG_20200807_224354.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/9b8/IMG_20200807_224354.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/036/IMG_20200807_224414.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/036/IMG_20200807_224414.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '7.jpg', '7'),
(8, NULL, NULL, 'Laboratory for the Development and Transfer of Microfluidic Technologies (DTMT)', 'laboratory-for-the-development-and-transfer-of-microfluidic-technologies-dtmt', '<p>The Laboratory for the Development and Transfer of Microfluidic Technologies (DTMT) is a mega-laboratory operating as part of Lomonosov Institute of Fine Chemical Technologies. It was created to train masters and graduate students in modern microfluidic technologies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The main areas for the work of the laboratory</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Synthesis with precise control of conditions and detection of intermediates for the preparation and screening of new medicinal drugs.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Encapsulation of substances with a monomodal particle size distribution for the production of pharmaceutical preparations with durable effect.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Synthesis of polymeric nano- or microparticles-carriers with a monomodal particle size distribution.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Laboratory Skills</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The center of the laboratory is the Qmix Pro Ext automatic microreactor system for the synthesis and encapsulation of chemicals. The Qmix system is a universal microreactor tool for solving a number of tasks both for the synthesis of new and known pharmaceutical substances and for the production of their prolonged forms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks to the established system, students learn to work in a laboratory mode, conduct fundamental research and develop methods and technologies for the synthesis and encapsulation of substances. Also, in a pilot production mode, they learn to obtain substances and encapsulated forms of prolonged action.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Laboratory equipment</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Qmix Pro Ext Installation is an automated compact system of continuous flow-through microreactors (microchips) for working with liquids and gases.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Qmix system is a unique tool for continuous operation due to its absolutely pulsation-free dosing of liquids and gases. In Europe and the USA, leading chemical and pharmaceutical companies synthesize about 30% of products with the use of such systems. The advantages of microreactors are high selectivity, efficiency and safety of the processes, as well as the compact equipment. Currently, there are only 2 such laboratories in the Russian Federation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/1d0/Mikroflyuidika-oborudovanie.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/84f/Mikroflyuidnyy-khimicheskiy-reaktor.JPG\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/1d0/Mikroflyuidika-oborudovanie.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/84f/Mikroflyuidnyy-khimicheskiy-reaktor.JPG\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/134/Mikroflyuidika.jpg\" /></p>\r\n', '8.jpg', '8'),
(9, NULL, NULL, 'Mobile Robotics University Laboratory', 'mobile-robotics-university-laboratory', '<p>The Mobile Robotics University Laboratory is designed to teach students the fundamentals of programming mobile robots using Robotic Operating System (ROS) tools.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The laboratory has 12 work stations equipped with everything necessary for programming and servicing mobile robots. The core of the laboratory&#39;s park consists of 30 JetBot robots additionally equipped with laser rangefinders, RealSense depth cameras and MarvelMind precision ultrasonic navigation systems.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For the convenience of the students and trainers, a testing area of more than 20 sq. m is located in the center of the laboratory, which allows work out all typical assignments, such as telecontrol, movement along the route avoiding obstacles, as well as group control algorithms, including those based on artificial intelligence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Moreover, the testing area is equipped with the system of video cameras and projectors that allow the elements of augmented reality to be projected onto the surface where robots are moving.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/583/1_0.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/583/1_0.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/3b8/1_1.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/3b8/1_1.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/404/1_2.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/404/1_2.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/b60/1_3.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/b60/1_3.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/772/1_4.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/772/1_4.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/359/1_5.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/359/1_5.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/7b2/1_6.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/7b2/1_6.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/dde/1_7.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/dde/1_7.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n', '9.jpg', '9'),
(10, NULL, NULL, 'Research and Educational Center for Biosynthesis, Isolation and Purification of Monoclonal Antibodies (Generium)', 'research-and-educational-center-for-biosynthesis-isolation-and-purification-of-monoclonal-antibodies-generium', '<p>The Research and Educational Center for Biosynthesis, Isolation and Purification of Monoclonal Antibodies (Generium) is a mega laboratory that was opened at the Department of Biotechnology and Industrial Pharmacy of Lomonosov Institute of Fine Chemical Technologies. It was created for the targeted training of highly qualified personnel for the biopharmaceutical industry.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Main areas of the laboratory work</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Development and production of a new generation of immunobiological preparations based on monoclonal antibodies.</li>\r\n	<li>Cultivation of mammalian cells and chromatographic purification of recombinant proteins.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Skills to be acquired in the Laboratory</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Research and Educational Center has its own targeted curriculum. Its development involved specialists from the companies &ndash; leaders of the domestic market in the field of biotechnological development and production of pharmaceuticals, in particular, Generium JSC, as well as international manufacturers of pharmaceutical equipment for bioprocesses: Global Life Science Solutions RUS LLC, Sartorius LLC Stedim RUS and JSC 3M Russia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The program includes a lecture course and practical training. The one-of-a-kind lecture course was created by the staff lecturers of RTU MIREA with the support of the leading specialists of Generium JSC. Students get practical skills in a new research and educational laboratory equipped with modern research and technological equipment. The curriculum also presupposes the implementation of qualifying master&#39;s theses by students on current issues of the biopharmaceutical sector.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The development and production of a new generation of immunobiological drugs based on monoclonal antibodies is currently one of the most advanced areas in the biopharmaceutical sector. However, enterprises in this fast-growing sector are experiencing a shortage of high-quality personnel. Therefore, the research and educational center, on the one hand, is a guarantee that the current needs of employers to graduates be satisfied, on the other, it provides the timely training of specialists whose knowledge and skills are in high demand by the industry.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Laboratory equipment</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The laboratory is equipped with modern tools and devices for modeling the production and purification of monoclonal antibodies, which allows to effectively select students and offer targeted training of specialists who have a theoretical background and practical skills to solve problems in real production.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Partner company</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>GENERIUM is a full-cycle research and production company, a leader in the orphan segment of the Russian pharmaceutical market.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The company has its own R&amp;D park capable of developing any biotechnological drug from the creation of a molecule to the start of industrial production. Individual drug research is carried out in collaboration with leading biotechnology companies and research institutes around the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/f69/R8A8718.JPG\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/a31/R8A8786.JPG\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/f69/R8A8718.JPG\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/a31/R8A8786.JPG\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/492/R8A8788.JPG\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/b3f/R8A8788_1.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/c11/RTU08083.JPG\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/bd7/RTU08085.JPG\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/050/RTU08087.JPG\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/8a2/RTU08089.JPG\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/0fc/RTU08249.JPG\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '10.jfif', '10'),
(11, NULL, NULL, 'Radio electronic Technologies Megalaboratory', 'radio-electronic-technologies-megalaboratory', '<p>The Institute of Radio Engineering and Telecommunication Systems has created a universal research and technical center for the continuous development of radio electronic technologies - the Radio electronic technologies mega laboratory. This is a single complex of interconnected coordinated laboratories which are equipped with all the necessary equipment for practice-oriented teaching and research activity on modern advanced technologies and technologies of the future.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At the moment, the center has several laboratories:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. The Laboratory for digital design and modeling of radio electronic equipment is equipped with high-performance workstations and professional systems for computer-aided design of electronic equipment at various design levels for &quot;paperless&quot; product design.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/ed1/1.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/ed1/1.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/95a/2.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/95a/2.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. The Laboratory for the assembly and installation of radio-electronic means is equipped with devices for prototyping printed circuit boards for various purposes; digital files using subtractive or additive technologies are applied, assembly and assembly equipment for hot-air and infrared soldering of products is used, as well as a section for machining and prototyping of body products.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/d92/3.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/b5c/3_1_.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/975/4.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/975/4.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. The Specialized laboratory of technological processes for the production of radio-electronic equipment has the tools and devices for automated climatic, mechanical, structural tests of radio-electronic means; optical three-dimensional and microimaging control; manual line surface mount.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/5dd/5.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/f00/6.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/5dd/5.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/f00/6.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/9b6/7.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/a70/8.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/9cc/9.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/856/10.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/a47/11.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/8b5/12.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/582/13.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/bc0/14.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/f44/15.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/1f0/16.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. The Laboratory for tuning and adjusting radio electronic equipment has the necessary radio measuring devices for tuning and adjusting the radio technical parameters of finished products, troubleshooting for the repair and maintenance of the equipment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/021/17.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/021/17.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Laboratory for 3D prototyping and control of multilayer printed circuit boards is equipped with unique devices for printed electronics on a 3D printer of multilayer printed circuit boards, JTAG systems for boundary scanning of complex digital products, stands for monitoring the parameters of a passive electronic component base in miniature cases and probe stations, an in-circuit control system with flying probes for compliance with design documentation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/327/19.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/63a/23.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/327/19.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/63a/23.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/c94/21.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/348/22.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/de2/24.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/59a/20.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/ab8/18.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the near future, it is planned to expand the Radio electronic Technologies Mega-laboratory by commissioning new laboratories:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>radio wave processes and microwave modules</li>\r\n	<li>three-dimensional diagrams on plastics and flexible carriers</li>\r\n	<li>electromagnetic compatibility of radio electronic equipment</li>\r\n	<li>radio monitoring and telemetry</li>\r\n	<li>micro-assemblies and systems in the case</li>\r\n	<li>printed circuit boards and modules with electrical and optical connections</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '11.jpg', '11');

