(4, NULL, NULL, 'RTU MIREA participated in Education and Career international exhibition held in the Republic of Belarus', '<p>Between February 18 and 20, representatives of RTU MIREA took part in the 19th&nbsp;<em>Education and Career</em>&nbsp;international specialized exhibition for schoolchildren, applicants, students and parents which was held in Minsk, the Republic of Belarus. RTU MIREA was represented by the delegation members I.S. Solunova, Deputy First Vice Rector, and E.A. Slyozkina, Deputy Director of the Institute of International Education. More than 30 universities from Russia and over 50 educational institutions from Belarus took part in the exhibition.</p>\n\n<p>It is the first time that the exhibition demonstrated the stands of the Russian Ministry of Education and Science and the Representative Office of Rossotrudnichestvo (Federal Agency for Affairs of the Commonwealth of Independent States, Compatriots Residing Abroad and International Humanitarian Co-Operation) in the Republic of Belarus &ndash; the Russian Center for Science and Culture in Minsk (RCSC). Eduard Feliksovich Krustkaln, Head of the RCSC had a series of working meetings with representatives of universities of the Russian Federation where they discussed possible formats of cooperation and mapped out a plan for implementation of joint projects.</p>\n\n<p>Within three days, over 11,000 people from Minsk, Vitebsk, Brest, Gomel, Grodno, Mogilev attended the exhibition. The RTU MIREA stand evoked great interest among applicants planning to continue their studies in Russia. Everyone could personally talk to the representatives of the University, ask questions, and get all the necessary information about the rules of admission, conditions of study, and areas of training.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"upload/1709580584.jpg\" style=\"height:150px; width:200px\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"upload/624043518.jpg\" style=\"height:150px; margin-left:10px; margin-right:10px; width:200px\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"upload/692500410.jpg\" style=\"height:150px; width:113px\" /></p>\n', 'admin@edu.mirea.ru', 'March 12, 2021', 'rtu-mirea-participated-in-education-and-career-international-exhibition-held-in-the-republic-of-belarus', 'IMG_20210219_103514.jpg'),
(5, NULL, NULL, 'RTU MIREA Rector congratulates the staff, the faculty and the students of the University on Defender of the Fatherland Day', '<p>Dear colleagues!</p>\n\n<p>I congratulate you on Defender of the Fatherland Day!</p>\n\n<p>February 23 is a holiday of courageous people, true patriots of their country &ndash; of all those who have devoted their lives to the noble cause of serving their Motherland. This day is a symbol of the inextricable link between generations, the recognition by the people of great contributions of the Russian army.</p>\n\n<p>Defending one&rsquo;s Motherland in peacetime means working honestly for its prosperity honoring the glorious traditions of our fathers and grandfathers.</p>\n\n<p>On the eve of Defender of the Fatherland Day, I sincerely wish you good health, prosperity, resolution, determination and perseverance in achieving your goals for the benefit of our dear Motherland.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"upload/171657030.jpg\" style=\"height:467px; width:700px\" /></p>\n', 'admin@edu.mirea.ru', 'March 12, 2021', 'rtu-mirea-rector-congratulates-the-staff-the-faculty-and-the-students-of-the-university-on-defender-of-the-fatherland-day', '3_1_.jpg'),
(6, NULL, NULL, 'IIT students and staff received thanks and prizes from Samsung Electronics', '<p>On February 17, the faculty and the students of the Institute of Information Technologies, the winners in the third annual interuniversity competition of projects of graduates of Samsung IT Academy educational programs, received thanks and prizes from Samsung Electronics.</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Anton Nikolayevich Mironov, senior lecturer of the Department of Mathematical Support and Standardization of Information Technologies, was awarded a prize for fruitful cooperation and high level of training of students in the Internet of Things track.</li>\n	<li>Pavel Valerievich Stepanov, assistant professor of the Department of corporate information systems, also got an award for fruitful cooperation and high level of training of students in the Mobile Development track.</li>\n	<li>Alexander Levandrovsky received an award for the victory in the Samsung Special Nomination.</li>\n	<li>Danila Ostapenko, Nikita Ostapenko and Nikita Tumanov were awarded prizes for the second place in the Mobile Development track.</li>\n	<li>Vladislav Sakharov was awarded a prize for the victory in the Viewers&rsquo; Choice nomination.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>For the victory in the University of the Year nomination on behalf of RTU MIREA, the prizes were received by Andrey Sergeevich Zuev, Director of the Institute of Information Technologies. Two interactive displays &ndash; Samsung Flip 2 WM85R &ndash; will be installed after the completion of the repairs in the new classrooms of the Department of Mathematical Support and Standardization of Information Technologies.</p>\n\n<p>The event was held with the account of the current security measures, with a small number of guests invited.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"upload/1514374386.jpg\" style=\"height:133px; width:200px\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"upload/857805848.jpg\" style=\"height:133px; margin-left:10px; margin-right:10px; width:200px\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"upload/1094441459.jpg\" style=\"height:133px; width:200px\" /></p>\n', 'admin@edu.mirea.ru', 'March 12, 2021', 'iit-students-and-staff-received-thanks-and-prizes-from-samsung-electronics', 'IMG_5429.jpg'),
(7, NULL, NULL, 'A regular meeting of the scientific workshop guided by A.S. Sigov, President of RTU MIREA, was held online', '<p>On February 17, a regular meeting of the CMP (Condensed-matter physics) scientific workshop was held online under the guidance of A.S. Sigov, President of RTU MIREA.</p>\n\n<p>The speakers named below made their presentations:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>I.S. Ovchinnikov (RTU MIREA). &ldquo;Development of the method of atomic force microscopy to determine the mechanical properties of insulating dielectrics with low dielectric constant&rdquo;. The presentation was based on the materials of the Ph.D. thesis, technical sciences. Specialty: 05.27.06 &ldquo;Technology and equipment for the production of semiconductors, materials and electronic devices&rdquo;. Scientific adviser &ndash; K.A. Vorotylov.</li>\n	<li>V.I. Chukita (Transnistrian State University named after T.G. Shevchenko). &ldquo;Preparation and investigation of epitaxial layers of CdSe/mica for optoelectronic devices of solid-state electronics&rdquo;. The presentation was based on the materials of the Ph.D. thesis, physical and mathematical sciences. Specialty: 05.27.01 &ldquo;Solid-state electronics, radio electronic components, micro- and nanoelectronics, devices based on quantum effects&rdquo;. Scientific adviser &ndash; V.S. Feschenko.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Each presentation was followed by a discussion in which professors E.D. Mishina, M.S. Blanter, K.A. Vorotylov, A.N. Yurasov, associate professors I.V. Gladyshev and L.Yu. Fetisov, and other employees of the Department of Nanoelectronics, RTU MIREA Institute of Physics and Technology, took part.</p>\n\n<p>It was decided to approve in general these presentations and allow more time to make certain corrections to the texts with the consideration of the comments for the subsequent defense at the Dissertation Council of RTU MIREA D212.131.02.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"upload/57734735.jpg\" style=\"height:487px; width:700px\" /></p>\n', 'admin@edu.mirea.ru', 'March 12, 2021', 'a-regular-meeting-of-the-scientific-workshop-guided-by-a-s-sigov-president-of-rtu-mirea-was-held-online', 'MG_6015.jpg'),
(8, NULL, NULL, 'Department of General Chemical Technology of Lomonosov Institute of Fine Chemical Technologies renovated the laboratory resources', '<p>By the beginning of the spring semester of the current academic year at the Department of General Chemical Technology of Lomonosov Institute of Fine Chemical Technologies, two educational laboratories (O-505 and O-506) were renovated and equipped with new laboratory furniture and equipment:. In this very laboratory, a unique workshop dedicated to the technology of obtaining basic inorganic and organic substances will be held for undergraduate students in chemistry, chemical technology, biotechnology and materials science.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>The modern overhaul of laboratories and the new equipment will significantly improve the level of study and mastering the basics of chemical technology, as well as enhance students&rsquo; interest in the educational process.</p>\n\n<p>During the internship course, students will be able to quickly master the basic techniques necessary for the development of modern technological processes, and solve problems of fundamental nature. The Department of General Chemical Technology has also renovated two display classrooms, which will soon open.</p>\n\n<p>The Department of General Chemical Technology closely combines educational and scientific processes relating to the development and study of new catalysts and catalytic processes to produce organic and inorganic substances, solve problems of hydrogen energy and environmental problems at the highest modern level.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"upload/377251770.jpg\" style=\"height:467px; width:700px\" /></p>\n', 'admin@edu.mirea.ru', 'March 12, 2021', 'department-of-general-chemical-technology-of-lomonosov-institute-of-fine-chemical-technologies-renovated-the-laboratory-resources', 'IMG_0683.jpg'),
(9, NULL, NULL, 'Within the framework of the Year of Science and Technology, the Scientists to Schools campaign was launched', '<p>On February 12, within the framework of the Year of Science and Technology, the&nbsp;<em>Scientists to Schools</em>&nbsp;campaign was launched. More than 200 representatives of the academic community &ndash; from young scientists to academicians of the Russian Academy of Sciences &ndash; will inform students about the latest developments in science and research.</p>\n\n<p>Topical issues to be discussed:</p>\n\n<p>How was the Russian coronavirus vaccine created?</p>\n\n<p>What is the way to see the Universe and &ldquo;make friends&rdquo; with neutrinos?</p>\n\n<p>What are modern batteries made of?</p>\n\n<p>These issues and many others will be covered in the course of the event.</p>\n\n<p>Moscow and Moscow Region, the Trans-Baikal Territory, the Stavropol Territory, Orenburg, Volgograd, Sverdlovsk and Rostov Regions, the Republic of Sakha (Yakutia), the Republic of Tatarstan and other regions of Russia have joined the action.</p>\n\n<p>The organizers of the All-Russian Scientists to Schools event are the Ministry of Education and Science of Russia, the Russian Union of Rectors (RUR) with the support of the NAUKA 0+ project.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"upload/201071018.jpg\" style=\"height:467px; width:700px\" /></p>\n', 'admin@edu.mirea.ru', 'March 12, 2021', 'within-the-framework-of-the-year-of-science-and-technology-the-scientists-to-schools-campaign-was-launched', '0fl3YXe6PmE.jpg'),
(10, NULL, NULL, 'Felicitations on the Day of Russian Science by Stanislav Alekseevich Kudzh', '<p>Dear colleagues, the faculty, the students and graduate students of MIREA &ndash; Russian Technological University!</p>\n\n<p>I sincerely congratulate you on the Day of Russian Science!</p>\n\n<p>The year of 2021 is declared the Year of Science and Technology. I believe that this decision of the President of Russia is extremely important not only for our national science, but also for the country at large, all sectors of the Russian economy and walks of our life.</p>\n\n<p>The COVID-19 epidemic, which the civilization is facing today, has very clearly demonstrated the great importance of science and technology, for many it has become obvious how important it is to develop this sphere. The goal for us is to be able to always promptly respond to any dangerous situations, the foundation, that is the accumulated knowledge should be in place.</p>\n\n<p>This year we need to provide fundamental science with a worthy resource for development. Today, in addition to the epidemic, we face a number of serious challenges, and only science can give an adequate response to them.<br />\n⠀<br />\nYou and I have something to be rightfully proud of: the coronavirus vaccine developed with the participation of RTU MIREA employees, has become a sensation for the whole world. Our colleagues also have amazing breakthrough works in various fields of research: applied mathematics, physics, and materials science.<br />\n⠀<br />\nOne of the main tasks of the Year of Science is to raise the prestige of science in the eyes of young people. At the same time, we must treat with respect and well-deserved recognition the achievements of our &ldquo;golden fund&rdquo;, those scholars who in the most difficult crisis years stayed in the country and preserved the Russian science while doing world-scale research.</p>\n\n<p>Throughout its history, our University has been famous for outstanding researchers and academic schools. Today we are training personnel for the Russian economy in specialties that, I am sure, will be in high demand in future!</p>\n\n<p>With all my heart, I wish all scientists of today and the future good health, inexhaustible vitality, inspiration and success in work, new victories and discoveries!</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"upload/1299435522.jpg\" style=\"height:467px; width:700px\" /></p>\n', 'admin@edu.mirea.ru', 'March 12, 2021', 'felicitations-on-the-day-of-russian-science-by-stanislav-alekseevich-kudzh', '4-_1_.jpg'),
(11, NULL, NULL, 'Valery Falkov, Minister of Science and Higher Education of the Russian Federation, congratulated the academic and educational community on the Day of Russian Science', '<p>Valery Falkov, Minister of Science and Higher Education of the Russian Federation, congratulated the academic and educational community on the Day of Russian Science.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://youtu.be/9G4f7ZXbprs\">https://youtu.be/9G4f7ZXbprs</a></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"upload/92573306.jpg\" style=\"height:700px; width:700px\" /></p>\n', 'admin@edu.mirea.ru', 'March 12, 2021', 'valery-falkov-minister-of-science-and-higher-education-of-the-russian-federation-congratulated-the-academic-and-educational-community-on-the-day-of-russian-science', 'c140f09b7589febb5c44d59c96a82064.jpg'),
(12, NULL, NULL, 'Felicitations on the Day of Russian Science by Alexander Sergeevich Sigov', '<p>20 years ago, on the Day of Russian Science, everyone who had any relation to science, felt painfully ashamed and bitter. These days are, fortunately, in the past. Now we do have achievements to be proud of.</p>\n\n<p>The changes are indeed enormous: both with regard to the amount of funding, and the attitude of the Government to scientists, to our ideas and developments. But one of the main sorrows of the Russian science is that only the budget remains the single source of its financing. There are two aspects to it: on the one hand, it is not limitless, and &ldquo;Bolivar cannot carry double&rdquo;; still the more so, if we speak of science, the defense complex, the social sphere, and all the rest. On the other hand, the state is holding back the creation of incentive mechanisms for business, while such mechanism should take on the lion&rsquo;s share of spendings on science.</p>\n\n<p>The Year of Science and Technology announced by the President of the Russian Federation is a good driver to solve many problems in 2021: introduce new instruments for business investment in science, de-bureaucratize science and offer new opportunities for our scientists.</p>\n\n<p>Russian science, despite all the difficulties of growth, is a global brand, and our success in creating a vaccine against coronavirus has brilliantly demonstrated this to everyone. We are able to strike the minds of the world with scientific discoveries in all fields of knowledge, it is necessary that not only the government, but also those in public service be on the side of science.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Congratulations on our holiday, dear colleagues!</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"upload/1854667287.jpg\" style=\"height:586px; width:700px\" /></p>\n', 'admin@edu.mirea.ru', 'March 12, 2021', 'felicitations-on-the-day-of-russian-science-by-alexander-sergeevich-sigov', 'sigov2.jpg'),
(13, NULL, NULL, 'Students of the Institute of Innovative Technologies and Public Administration participated in the webinar of the London School of Digital Business', '<p>On February 4, students of the Institute of Innovative Technologies and Public Administration participated in the&nbsp;<em>How to activate the abilities to achieve prosperity and success webinar?</em>&nbsp;(The secret of genius for a wealthier and happier you!) from the London School of Digital Business (LSDB).</p>\n\n<p>The key-note speaker at the event was Louise Mosley, business coach, founder of the NB Coaching Academy.</p>\n\n<p>The attention of the webinar participants was focused on issues of introspection and self-esteem, techniques for revealing their talent, and how to use it to enhance their productivity and ensure professional success and personal happiness.</p>\n\n<p>The event was held in English, which allowed its participants not only to deepen their knowledge of self-management, but also to develop their listening skills.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"upload/882843062.jpg\" style=\"height:307px; width:700px\" /></p>\n', 'admin@edu.mirea.ru', 'March 12, 2021', 'students-of-the-institute-of-innovative-technologies-and-public-administration-participated-in-the-webinar-of-the-london-school-of-digital-business', 'SHkola.jpg'),
(14, NULL, NULL, 'More information about the life at RTU MIREA is now available in the Telegram channel', '<p>Do you wish to receive more exciting and useful information about the events at RTU MIREA?</p>\n\n<p>Find all the latest news, urgent announcements and the most important information on the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://t.me/rtumirea_official\">RTU MIREA Telegram channel</a>.</p>\n\n<p>Subscribe to the channel and learn more about the life at RTU MIREA!</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"upload/1922204297.jpg\" style=\"height:394px; width:700px\" /></p>\n', 'admin@edu.mirea.ru', 'March 12, 2021', 'more-information-about-the-life-at-rtu-mirea-is-now-available-in-the-telegram-channel', 'Telegram_kanal.jpg'),
(15, NULL, NULL, 'Graduates of the IRTS Specialist’s programs received diplomas', '<p>Do you wish to receive more exciting and useful information about the events at RTU MIREA?</p>\n\n<p>On February 2, a graduation procedure was held for students of the Specialist&rsquo;s programs of the Institute of Radio Engineering and Telecommunication Systems.</p>\n\n<p>Stanislav Alekseevich Kudzh, Rector of RTU MIREA, and Aleksandr Sergeevich Sigov, President of the University, handed diplomas magna cum laude to the best graduates and congratulated them on this significant event. The procedure was followed by the valedictory by Andrey Georgievich Vasiliev, Director of the Institute.</p>\n\n<p>Good luck to you, dear graduates!</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"upload/1798111711.jpg\" style=\"height:467px; width:700px\" /></p>\n', 'admin@edu.mirea.ru', 'March 12, 2021', 'graduates-of-the-irts-specialist’s-programs-received-diplomas', 'Vruchenie_diplomov_3pr.jpg'),
(16, NULL, NULL, 'The meeting between RTU MIREA and the Combat Brotherhood non-commercial organization of war veterans signed a cooperation agreement', '<p>A working meeting was held between Stanislav Alekseevich Kudzh, Rector of RTU MIREA, Dmitry Vadimovich Sablin, State Duma Deputy, and Evgeny Aleksandrovich Binyukov, Head of the Expeditionary Combat Readiness Center of the Ministry of Defense of the Russian Federation.</p>\n\n<p>During the discussion, an exchange of views took place on new approaches and methods to form a sense of civic responsibility and patriotism in young people.</p>\n\n<p>Representatives of the Combat Brotherhood spoke about their experience in keeping traditions, military-patriotic and historical education of the younger generation, shared many years of expertise in organizing&nbsp; events in this sphere. Dmitry Vadimovich Sablin gave the representatives and students of RTU MIREA a tour of the&nbsp;<em>Combat Brotherhood</em>&nbsp;museum and showed an exposition dedicated to the veterans of local military conflicts.</p>\n\n<p>The delegation from RTU MIREA offered information on similar programs carried out at our University:&nbsp;<em>Summer in Special Operations Forces, Scout&rsquo;s Trail</em>, diving and airsoft clubs, a youth army division and a historical search unit, as well as the University&rsquo;s plans to improve this work in 2021.</p>\n\n<p>Evgeny Aleksandrovich Binyukov, Head of the Expeditionary Combat Readiness Center of the Ministry of Defense, spoke about the activities in this area carried out by the Ministry of Defense of the Russian Federation and the Russian Geographical Society.</p>\n\n<p>The participants in the work meeting stated that it is necessary to develop new projects and improve the already existing programs, implement innovative methods and principles which have become the subject matter of the dialogue between the partners and the basis for expanding partnership.</p>\n\n<p>As a result of the meeting, an agreement was signed on cooperation between RTU MIREA and the Combat Brotherhood, All-Russian public organization of veterans. Also, Stanislav Alekseevich Kudzh and Evgeny Aleksandrovich Binyukov signed a plan of major events for 2021, which includes joint expeditions of the Expeditionary Center of the Russian Ministry of Defense and RTU MIREA to the Kuril Islands, an underwater search for sunken objects of the Great Patriotic War and many other projects.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"upload/755000909.jpg\" style=\"height:133px; width:200px\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"upload/2004218725.jpg\" style=\"height:133px; margin-left:10px; margin-right:10px; width:200px\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"upload/936612812.jpg\" style=\"height:133px; width:200px\" /></p>\n', 'admin@edu.mirea.ru', 'March 12, 2021', 'the-meeting-between-rtu-mirea-and-the-combat-brotherhood-non-commercial-organization-of-war-veterans-signed-a-cooperation-agreement', '1.jpg'),
(17, NULL, NULL, 'Ministry of Education and Science of the Russian Federation: from February 8, universities return to the traditional format of education', '<p>A working meeting was held between Stanislav Alekseevich Kudzh, Rector of RTU MIREA, Dmitry Vadimovich Sablin, State Duma Deputy, and Evgeny Aleksandrovich Binyukov, Head of the Expeditionary Combat Readiness Center of the Ministry of Defense of the Russian Federation.</p>\n\n<p>During the discussion, an exchange of views took place on new approaches and methods to form a sense of civic responsibility and patriotism in young people.</p>\n\n<p>The&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/upload/medialibrary/71f/28.01.2021_63.pdf\">Order</a>&nbsp;was signed by Valery Falkov, Head of the Russian Ministry of Education and Science.</p>\n\n<p>The document instructs heads of universities under the jurisdiction of the Ministry of Education and Science of the Russian Federation to resume training in the traditional format; the decision was taken with the account of the opinion of student councils and in agreement with the territorial bodies of Rospotrebnadzor (Russian Consumer Protection Agency), as well as the specifics of the prevalence of coronavirus infection in a particular region.</p>\n\n<p>At the same time, universities need to take preventive measures recommended for compliance with Rospotrebnadzor, namely, to: create conditions for hygienic treatment of hands with antiseptic agents, ensure contactless body temperature control of all persons belonging to the organization, observance of the mask regime and social distancing, airing classrooms during the breaks. Persons with signs of infectious diseases shall not be admitted to the premises of the University.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"upload/1366673837.jpg\" style=\"height:467px; width:700px\" /></p>\n', 'admin@edu.mirea.ru', 'March 12, 2021', 'ministry-of-education-and-science-of-the-russian-federation-from-february-8-universities-return-to-the-traditional-format-of-education', 'MIREA.jpg'),
(18, NULL, NULL, 'RTU MIREA summed up the results of the Student and Teacher of the Year 2020 competition', '<p>The Student and Teacher of the Year 2020 competition has ended at RTU MIREA. Several months of preparation, registration of competition documents and interviews in 11 nominations helped to identify the best of the best.</p>\n\n<p>Our hearty congratulations to the winners:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Student public figure of the year - Anastasia Olegovna Podogova</li>\n	<li>The Intellectual of the Year - Rustam Uralovich Astafiev</li>\n	<li>Creative Image of the Year - Ivan Igorevich Pogrebnyak</li>\n	<li>Volunteer of the Year - Tatiana Yurievna Soboleva</li>\n	<li>Sports Image of the Year - Artyom Igorevich Dvoinikov</li>\n	<li>Young Scholar of the Year - Ksenia Aleksandrovna Zhdanova</li>\n	<li>Lecturer of the Year - Evgeny Vladimirovich Kashkin</li>\n	<li>Student of the College of Instrumentation and Information Technologies - Kristina Vladimirovna Ermachkova</li>\n	<li>Student of the Year at the Military Training Center - Vladislav Andreevich Khusnutdinov</li>\n	<li>Student of the Year of the RTU MIREA branch - Alena Vladimirovna Golovina</li>\n	<li>International Student of the Year - Martin Chayo Fernandez</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Also, the winners in two special nominations were:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Prize of the President of RTU MIREA - Andrey Kirillovich Kulikov</li>\n	<li>Audience Choice Award - Anastasia Nikolaevna Sukhorukova.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>We wish the winners of the competition and all the lecturers, professors, trainers and students every success!</p>\n\n<p>The final part of the competition was held for the first time in an online format, the recording can be viewed at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?utm_source=mirea&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=news&amp;v=LJcpmOnL6s8&amp;feature=youtu.be\">the link</a>&nbsp;below.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"upload/1297714118.jpg\" style=\"height:133px; width:200px\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"upload/764359020.jpg\" style=\"height:133px; margin-left:10px; margin-right:10px; width:133px\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"upload/2075324246.jpg\" style=\"height:133px; width:200px\" /></p>\n', 'admin@edu.mirea.ru', 'March 12, 2021', 'rtu-mirea-summed-up-the-results-of-the-student-and-teacher-of-the-year-2020-competition', 'Foto_12.jpg'),
(19, NULL, NULL, 'Starting from February 9, RTU MIREA sets to resume full-time classes with only lectures remaining on-line', '<p>Starting from February 9, RTU MIREA partially resumes full-time education. This will include seminar-type classes for which students must come to the University. Participation in regular in-class seminars is mandatory for students. Most of the lectures, however, as well as classes for correspondence and evening groups, will so far be held in a distance format.</p>\n\n<p>The timetable will be available in the appropriate section of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.mirea.ru/schedule/\">website</a></p>\n\n<p>Information on the procedure for the return of nonresident and foreign students to the RTU MIREA dormitories will be also published on the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://student.mirea.ru/\">website</a>.</p>\n\n<p>Classes for foreign students who are presently outside the Russian Federation and cannot yet enter its territory will be organized online.</p>\n\n<p>We would like to remind you that while at the University, you must maintain a social distance during classes and in public places.</p>\n\n<p>We urge everyone to follow the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://english.mirea.ru/covid/current-information/\">recommendations for the prevention of COVID-19</a>.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"upload/763511532.jpg\" style=\"height:467px; width:700px\" /></p>\n', 'admin@edu.mirea.ru', 'March 13, 2021', 'starting-from-february-9-rtu-mirea-sets-to-resume-full-time-classes-with-only-lectures-remaining-on-line', 'DSC_1712.jpg');

